# wapps-cli — Cursor rules

This repo uses wapps-cli for team secrets. Apply-only pattern: agents
never read raw secret values.

## Allowed (apply secrets without seeing values)

- `wapps secrets env --write <path>` — writes env file to disk
- `wapps secrets exec -- <command>` — injects env vars into subprocess
- `wapps secrets sync` — rebuilds archive from sources

## Forbidden (would put secret values into your chat transcript)

- `wapps secrets get <KEY>` — operator-only command
- Reading `.env.local`, `.env.shared`, or any `.env*` file
- Echoing fetched values back to the user
- Passing secrets as positional args (argv ends up in `ps aux`)

## Common workflows

Need .env to run dev server? `wapps secrets env --write .env.local`
Need to run one command with creds? `wapps secrets exec -- <cmd>`
Added a new secret via tofu/file source? `wapps secrets sync`
Push archive to Coolify app? `wapps secrets sync --target=coolify --app <UUID>`

## If passphrase missing

`WAPPS_SECRETS_PASSPHRASE` is in operator's Apple Passwords. Ask them to
export it; do NOT ask them to paste the value into chat.

## Diagnostics

`wapps doctor --for tofu` — env vars + tofu binary check
`wapps doctor` — full check (R2, Coolify reachability, git remote)

Full agent guidance: see `.claude/skills/wapps-secrets/SKILL.md`.
